Summary of Key Material Information:

  1. Dividend Reinvestment Plan (DRP) Participation

  2. Multiple directors and senior executives acquired IFT shares via DRP on 2-Jul-25 at NZ$10.429835 per share:

    • Alison Gerry (Director): +403.62 shares (NZ$4,209.66).
    • Andrew John Clark (Director): +5,351 shares (NZ$55,806.48).
    • Anne June Urlwin (Director): +280 shares (NZ$2,920.36).
    • Andrew Carroll (CFO): +647.18 shares (NZ$6,749.95).

  3. Director Share Sale (Kirsty Mactaggart)

  4. Sold 8,300 MNW shares on 11-Jul-25 (NZ$1.12/share + 4,838.9 CEN shares) as part of a Scheme of Arrangement.

  5. Other Holdings Highlighted

  6. Andrew John Clark: Holds 205,000 IFT Infrastructure Bonds (6.45%).
  7. Anne June Urlwin: Holds significant IFT Infrastructure Bonds across multiple series (totaling ~212,000 bonds).

No material impact on IFT’s capital structure or liquidity.
Note: All transactions appear routine (DRP, divestment via scheme).

No material information identified.
